# DSM Ecosystem Path Registry

**Reference:** DSM_0.2 §18 (Ecosystem Path Registry)

Local configuration mapping logical ecosystem names to filesystem paths.
This file is gitignored per-instance. Each DSM installation (hub, spoke, or
cloned mirror) declares its own ecosystem layout here.

Cloned-Mirror Kick-off populates `dsm-central` with the clone's own repo root
(self-registration, so the clone becomes its own local ecosystem hub). Other
rows are added by the user if they maintain additional ecosystem members.

**Created:** {ISO_DATE}
**Instance type:** {cloned-mirror | hub | spoke}

## Paths

| Name | Path | Description | Mirror |
|------|------|-------------|--------|
| dsm-central | {REPO_ROOT} | Local DSM hub (this clone) | - |
| portfolio | {UPDATE THIS PATH OR REMOVE ROW} | Portfolio project for cross-repo notifications | - |
| contributions-docs | {UPDATE THIS PATH OR REMOVE ROW} | Governance folder for external contributions | - |

